<br>
Most people in guild have 6 AAs, a few of us have 50+.  Gearwise - we've got most of what we needed out of HoT, most of us wear HoT armor or better, however there's still some folks who could use some HoT armor, even tho the main core is all but done with it.<br>
<br>
Lots of Windblades, most have epics etc.  Sorry for the blah blah blah just trying to best inform you of what we got.<br>
<br>
So for our best accomplishment has been Derakor the Vindicator.  I think our biggest problem is getting 20+ people online at a time.  Which is mainly why I'm trying to get a feel from you guys on what NToV woudl require numberwise, as well as class-wise.<br>
<br>
Thanx for your help.<br>
<br>
Ace<br>
Knights of the White Rose <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alodarnsoulburner>Alodarn Soulburner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 184<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/27/03 9:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: NToV Advice plz</span><hr size=1> Sounds like your very close to being ready.<br>
Back when I was in NToV, Dragonbane really helped, not sure now, as 65 and the new spells have changed the game quite a bit. All depends on the resists.<br>
<br>
I seem to remember, some of the named had silly resists if you didn't get into melee range, that is unless you had DB.<br>
<br>
Apart from that, look up on the web and dig out some strat.<br>
<br>
Oh, and you will need multiple main tanks, as the &quot;flurries&quot; can chew a person up double time. (Not sure exactly what they did, but I think they took turns at tanking them using def)<br>
<br>
One last tip, for Aary, have one of the melees call the AoE, and duck out DB and duck back, his aoe owns wizzys.....<br>
<br>
